Browsing the Analytics Tab

Find the last report or dashboard that you worked with or see what’s available on the Analytics tab. Browse enables you to quickly locate the items you’re looking for by filtering through different categories.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group, Enterprise, Professional, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To browse the Analytics tab:
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards

To browse the Analytics tab with CRM Analytics items:
Use CRM Analytics

Click Browse that shows all your analytics organized by type. Within Browse are filters that set the current context and determine the results that are returned.
Click an asset filter to narrow down the browse page to a selection, then click additional filters to narrow your search further by date or owner.

Click column headers to sort search results in ascending or descending order.

Click Details in the row-action menu to view asset metadata.
title: Understanding Salesforce Analytics and Browsing
